♪ I'M IN DEEP

03:59.413 --> 04:01.502
-GIRL: WHOA.
-WHAT WAS I THINKING?

04:01.632 --> 04:03.286
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I ENTERED THIS TOURNAMENT.

04:03.417 --> 04:05.027
I CAN'T COMPETE
AT THIS LEVEL.

04:05.157 --> 04:07.203
-TRUST ME,
YOU'RE A NATURAL.

04:07.334 --> 04:10.119
-NO, NO, NO, NO.
JAMIE DUNCAN IS A NATURAL.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.990
I'LL NEVER TOUCH THAT.

04:12.121 --> 04:14.210
-HOBIE: JAMIE DUNCAN HASN'T
WON A TOURNAMENT FOR MONTHS.

04:14.341 --> 04:16.386
-SHE'S RANKED NUMBER
ONE IN THE WORLD, HOBIE.

04:16.517 --> 04:18.127
-YEAH, BUT NOT FOR LONG.

04:18.257 --> 04:20.521
SHE'S BEEN LAGGING
BIG TIME, LATELY.

04:20.651 --> 04:22.827
AND FROM WHAT I HEAR, SHE'S
GONNA LOSE ALL HER SPONSORS.

04:22.958 --> 04:24.873
AND IF THAT HAPPENS,
SHE'S HISTORY.

04:25.439 --> 04:27.876
SO YOU GOTTA REMEMBER THE
TWO MOST IMPORTANT THINGS:

04:28.006 --> 04:29.138
CONFIDENCE AND RHYTHM.

04:29.269 --> 04:30.357
STAY WITH THE FLOW
OF THE WAVE.

04:30.487 --> 04:32.141
[NEELY SIGHS]

04:39.366 --> 04:41.019
-ALL RIGHT,
HERE GOES NOTHING.

04:43.457 --> 04:45.502
-CHARGE IT!
[HANDS CLAP]

04:45.633 --> 04:50.768
[BEACHGOERS SHOUT]
[WAVES CRASH]

04:53.728 --> 04:55.295
[DOORBELL RINGS]

04:58.515 --> 05:00.212
-HEY, YOU, COME ON IN.
-SAMANTHA: HEY, READY TO GO?

05:00.343 --> 05:01.866
-OOH, YEAH, YOU WANT
A PIECE OF TOAST?

05:01.997 --> 05:03.694
-OH, NO THANKS, NOT
MUCH OF A BREAKFAST PERSON.

05:03.825 --> 05:05.305
-COME ON, BREAKFAST IS THE
MOST IMPORTANT MEAL OF THE DAY.

05:05.435 --> 05:07.394
-YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I HEAR.
SO, WHERE'S HOBIE?

05:07.524 --> 05:08.917
-HOBIE IS COACHING NEELY

05:09.047 --> 05:11.136
IN THE WILD WAHINE
BODY BOARD TOURNAMENT.

05:12.268 --> 05:14.749
-SO, WE HAVE THE
PLACE ALL TO OURSELVES?

05:14.879 --> 05:18.318
-WELL, WE DO HAVE TO BE AT
HEADQUARTERS IN 20 MINUTES.

05:18.448 --> 05:19.667
-GUESS YOU'LL HAVE
TO SKIP BREAKFAST.

05:19.797 --> 05:21.364
-MITCH: I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

05:21.495 --> 05:24.324
[MITCH MOANS ENTHUSIASTICALLY]
[SAMANTHA LAUGHS]

05:24.454 --> 05:29.024
[BEACHGOERS CHATTER]

05:30.286 --> 05:32.897
-NEWMIE: ALL RIGHT, LET'S SEE
WHAT WE HAVE GOING HERE, TODAY.

05:33.028 --> 05:37.337
OH, MY,
WHAT HAVE WE GOT HERE?

05:40.296 --> 05:42.342
-LET ME SEE, LET ME SEE.

05:48.173 --> 05:50.959
-COWABUNGA.

05:51.089 --> 05:52.656
-MANNY: COME ON,
NEWMIE, LET ME SEE.

05:53.396 --> 05:55.355
-ALL RIGHT, KID,
BUT MAKE IT QUICK.

05:57.835 --> 05:59.707
-MANNY: OH, QUE BUENA!

06:01.099 --> 06:02.710
OH, SHE'S A BABE!

06:03.406 --> 06:05.234
-THAT IS NOT A BABE.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.976
THAT IS A GODDESS.

06:10.152 --> 06:12.633
HEY, CODY, COME HERE.

06:12.763 --> 06:14.286
COME CHECK THIS OUT.

06:15.331 --> 06:17.377
-YOU SHOULD TAKE A COLD DIP
AND QUIT TORTURING YOURSELF.

06:17.507 --> 06:19.204
-HEY, THIS IS DIFFERENT.

06:19.901 --> 06:22.382
THIS GIRL IS EVERYTHING
THAT I HAVE EVER DREAMED OF.

06:23.557 --> 06:24.906
I THINK I'M IN LOVE.

06:25.515 --> 06:26.864
-I'LL BE THE JUDGE OF THAT.
LET ME IN THERE.

06:26.995 --> 06:28.518
MOVE IT, ROOKIE.

06:30.259 --> 06:32.261
-SHE'S FINE.

06:32.392 --> 06:33.871
-NEWMIE: WHAT DO YOU THINK?
[CODY LAUGHS]

06:35.830 --> 06:37.309
-FORGET IT, NEWMIE.

06:37.440 --> 06:39.486
NO OFFENSE, BUT SHE'S
WAY OUTTA YOUR LEAGUE.

06:42.532 --> 06:44.142
-GOOD MORNING, GUYS.

06:44.273 --> 06:46.406
-YEAH, THAT IS DEFINITELY
A BIG RIP DEVELOPING.

06:46.536 --> 06:47.885
-YEAH.
-GOOD MORNING, CAPTAIN.

06:49.887 --> 06:51.628
-UH, NEWMIE,
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND,

06:51.759 --> 06:52.803
MANNY'S GONNA JOIN YOU FOR
A LITTLE ON-THE-JOB TRAINING.

06:52.934 --> 06:54.588
-NO, NOT AT ALL.

06:54.718 --> 06:56.590
-OKAY, YOU WILL
BE IN TOWER FOUR.

06:56.720 --> 06:58.679
-FOUR?
-IS THAT A PROBLEM?

06:58.809 --> 07:02.596
-WELL, ALL THE ACTION'S
GONNA BE HERE AT 14 TODAY,

07:02.726 --> 07:05.076
THAT'S WHERE YOU'RE GONNA WANT
YOUR MOST EXPERIENCED PEOPLE.

07:05.207 --> 07:06.861
-"THE ACTION."

07:06.991 --> 07:09.559
WHAT SORT OF "ACTION"
WOULD YOU BE REFERRING TO?

07:10.865 --> 07:12.170
-UH...

07:12.301 --> 07:14.825
RIPS AND STUFF.

07:30.580 --> 07:32.103
-NEWMAN, I'D LIKE TO
SEE YOU IN MY OFFICE

07:32.234 --> 07:34.889
WHEN YOUR SHIFT AT
TOWER FOUR ENDS.

07:36.847 --> 07:39.241
[CODY AND MANNY SNICKER]

07:40.372 --> 07:41.896
-"RIPS AND STUFF"?

07:42.026 --> 07:43.463
[CODY LAUGHS]

07:45.595 --> 07:48.206
[TELEPHONE RINGS]
[RADIO CHATTERS]

07:48.337 --> 07:49.991
-HEARD YOU CAME DOWN
REAL HARD ON NEWMIE.

07:50.121 --> 07:52.123
-HIS JOB'S TO SAVE LIVES,
NOT PICK UP CHICKS.

07:52.254 --> 07:53.821
-MITCH: HE'S BEEN A
LIFEGUARD FOR 20 YEARS,

07:53.951 --> 07:55.692
I'M SURE HE KNOWS
WHAT HIS JOB IS.

07:55.823 --> 07:57.738
-ALL THE MORE REASON FOR HIM
TO ACT LIKE A PROFESSIONAL.

07:57.868 --> 07:59.348
ESPECIALLY AROUND MANNY,
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE

07:59.479 --> 08:01.132
A POSITIVE INFLUENCE
ON THE JUNIOR GUARDS.

08:01.263 --> 08:02.612
-MITCH: WHY ARE YOU MAKING
SUCH A BIG DEAL ABOUT THIS?

08:02.743 --> 08:04.005
-SAMANTHA: BECAUSE
IT IS A BIG DEAL.

08:04.135 --> 08:05.485
-MITCH: IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

08:06.311 --> 08:08.749
-IT'S HAPPENING.
-WHAT'S HAPPENING?

08:08.879 --> 08:10.664
-EXACTLY WHAT
I SAID WOULD HAPPEN.

08:10.794 --> 08:12.361
BECOMING ROMANTICALLY INVOLVED

08:12.492 --> 08:14.102
IS AFFECTING OUR ABILITY
TO WORK TOGETHER.

08:14.232 --> 08:16.321
-IT'S NOT AFFECTING ANYTHING.

08:16.452 --> 08:17.845
-THIS IS HOW IT
STARTED WITH ADAM.

08:17.975 --> 08:19.542
WE STARTED BICKERING
ABOUT LITTLE THINGS.

08:19.673 --> 08:20.891
-WE'RE NOT BICKERING.

08:21.022 --> 08:22.414
-SAMANTHA: YES, WE ARE.
-NO, WE'RE NOT.

08:22.545 --> 08:23.633
-WHAT DO YOU CALL THIS?

08:24.504 --> 08:26.593
[MITCH SIGHS]
-BICKERING.

08:31.075 --> 08:35.863
[PIPING MUSIC]
[PEOPLE CHATTER]

08:40.476 --> 08:41.869
[MAN GRUNTS]

08:41.999 --> 08:43.653
-MAN: ARE YOU
CRAZY OR SOMETHING?

08:48.092 --> 08:49.790
[JAMIE YELLS]

08:49.920 --> 08:51.792
-JAMIE: YOU COWARD!

09:14.597 --> 09:16.947
[JAMIE YELLS]
-MAN: OOH!

09:17.078 --> 09:18.645
OH, OW! OH, STOP!

09:18.775 --> 09:20.342
-WHY ARE YOU FOLLOWING ME, HUH?

09:20.472 --> 09:22.126
WHO SENT YOU, HUH?

09:22.257 --> 09:23.519
MY GRANDFATHER?

09:23.650 --> 09:24.520
-WHAT THE HELL'S
WRONG WITH YOU?

09:24.651 --> 09:26.043
HELP! STOP!

09:26.174 --> 09:27.175
HELP!
-JAMIE: ANSWER ME!

09:27.305 --> 09:28.829
-JAMIE: I SAID, WHO SENT YOU?

09:28.959 --> 09:30.091
-WHOA, WHOA!

09:30.221 --> 09:32.267
CODY, BACK UP.
-CODY: WHAT?

09:34.878 --> 09:36.314
-TAKE A LOOK AT THAT.

09:37.011 --> 09:38.665
[JAMIE YELLS]
-MAN: HELP!

09:40.754 --> 09:42.190
-THIS SHOULD BE FUN.

09:42.320 --> 09:44.061
-MAN: HELP!
[SIREN WAILS]

09:44.192 --> 09:46.498
[JAMIE SCREAMS]

09:46.629 --> 09:49.284
-WHAT'S WRO-- OW!

09:49.414 --> 09:50.590
STOP!

09:55.769 --> 09:57.597
-OH, MY GOD,
IT'S JAMIE DUNCAN!

09:57.727 --> 09:58.902
-CODY: YOU KNOW HER?

09:59.033 --> 10:00.556
[JAMIE SCREAMS INCOHERENTLY]

10:00.687 --> 10:02.079
-NEELY: JAMIE, STOP IT.
-CODY: WHAT'S GOING ON?

10:02.210 --> 10:03.603
-MAN: I DON'T KNOW.

10:03.733 --> 10:05.082
-NEELY: CALM DOWN,
JAMIE, I'VE GOT YOU.

10:05.213 --> 10:06.910
-MAN: I'M BLEEDING.
-CODY: LET ME SEE THAT.

10:07.041 --> 10:09.130
-JAMIE: WHAT DO YOU WANT?
WHO ARE YOU? MY MOTHER SEND YOU?

10:09.260 --> 10:11.480
-IT'S OKAY, I'M YOUR FRIEND.
-YOU'RE NOT MY FRIEND.

10:11.611 --> 10:13.438
I'VE NEVER SEEN YOU
BEFORE IN MY LIFE!

10:13.569 --> 10:15.223
LET GO OF ME.
LET GO OF ME!

10:15.353 --> 10:16.746
LET GO.

10:18.922 --> 10:21.316
[RUBBER TIRES SKID]

10:28.062 --> 10:29.541
-CODY: YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

10:29.672 --> 10:30.804
-MAN: HOW'S MY NOSE?
-CODY: WHAT HAPPENED?

10:30.934 --> 10:32.457
-MAN: MY NOSE, IS IT BROKEN?

10:32.588 --> 10:33.720
-CODY: NAH, IT'S ALL
RIGHT. SIR, WHAT HAPPENED?

10:33.850 --> 10:35.156
WHAT HAPPENED?
-MAN: I DON'T KNOW.

10:35.286 --> 10:36.636
THIS GIRL,
SHE STARTED BEATING ON ME,

10:36.766 --> 10:38.594
AND I THINK
I DISLOCATED MY SHOULDER.

10:40.944 --> 10:42.990
-ARE YOU SURE THAT WAS JAMIE
DUNCAN THE BODY BOARDER?

10:43.120 --> 10:44.731
-POSITIVE.

10:44.861 --> 10:46.515
-YOU THINK SHE'S ON
DRUGS, OR SOMETHING?

10:46.646 --> 10:47.995
-I DON'T KNOW.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.692
-TELL YOU ONE THING,

10:49.823 --> 10:51.912
I'D HATE TO TAKE OFF ON
A WAVE IN FRONT OF HER.

10:58.266 --> 11:04.011
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

11:07.101 --> 11:08.929
-HEY, NEWMIE, GUESS WHO'S BACK?

11:09.059 --> 11:10.495
-SHE'S ALL YOURS, KID.

11:10.626 --> 11:11.627
-WHAT? WAIT A MINUTE.

11:12.628 --> 11:13.934
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

11:14.064 --> 11:15.283
YESTERDAY YOU WERE
IN LOVE WITH HER.

11:15.413 --> 11:16.240
-HEY, YOU HEARD
CODY THE OTHER DAY,

11:16.371 --> 11:17.328
SHE'S OUTTA MY LEAGUE.

11:17.459 --> 11:19.287
10 YEARS AGO MAYBE, BUT NOW?

11:20.680 --> 11:22.682
THAT'S STRICTLY FANTASY TIME.

11:23.334 --> 11:24.379
-FANTASY?

11:24.509 --> 11:26.642
NEWMAN, YOU'RE A LIFEGUARD, MAN.

11:27.251 --> 11:28.731
YOU'RE A HERO.

11:29.471 --> 11:30.602
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO GET THE GIRL.

11:30.733 --> 11:31.691
[NEWMIE SCOFFS]

11:31.821 --> 11:33.214
-HATE TO TELL YOU THIS, KID,

11:33.344 --> 11:35.520
BUT IT DOESN'T ALWAYS
WORK OUT THAT WAY.

11:36.783 --> 11:38.610
-WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT, MAN?

11:39.481 --> 11:40.438
NEWMIE.

11:41.309 --> 11:44.138
[PEOPLE CHATTER]

11:44.268 --> 11:45.617
-ALL RIGHT, STARTS IN
A COUPLE OF MINUTES,

11:45.748 --> 11:46.923
GOTTA MAKE A SEVEN
OR MORE TO QUALIFY.

11:47.054 --> 11:47.881
GOOD LUCK.
-WOMAN: THANKS A LOT.

11:48.011 --> 11:49.970
-NAME?
-NEELY CAPSHAW.

11:50.100 --> 11:52.015
-IS THAT WITH A C OR A K?
-C.

11:54.191 --> 11:55.671
-HERE WE GO.

11:57.717 --> 11:59.588
I DON'T HAVE ANY MORE
SHIRTS, BUT UH...

11:59.719 --> 12:01.329
YOU LOOK PRETTY GOOD
IN BLACK AND PURPLE.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.681
HERE WE GO, QUALIFYING ROUND
STARTS IN A COUPLE MINUTES.

12:05.812 --> 12:07.988
YOU NEED A SEVEN OR MORE TO
MAKE THE CUT, ANY QUESTIONS?

12:08.118 --> 12:10.338
-YEAH, IS JAMIE DUNCAN AROUND?

12:10.468 --> 12:11.774
-I WISH.

12:12.427 --> 12:13.645
YOU A FRIEND OF HERS?
-NO, NO.

12:13.776 --> 12:15.343
I'M JUST A FAN.

12:15.473 --> 12:16.866
-WELL, IF YOU SEE HER,

12:16.997 --> 12:18.346
TELL HER TO GET HER
BUTT DOWN HERE, OKAY?

12:18.476 --> 12:19.956
I HAD A TV INTERVIEW
AND A PHOTO SHOOT

12:20.087 --> 12:21.523
LINED UP FOR THIS MORNING,
AND SHE STOOD ME UP.

12:21.653 --> 12:23.917
FREE PUBLICITY RIGHT
DOWN THE DRAIN.

12:24.700 --> 12:25.962
-IS SHE OKAY? IS EVERYTHING...

12:26.093 --> 12:27.311
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GOTTEN INTO HER.

12:27.964 --> 12:30.271
I GUESS ALL THE SUCCESS HAS
JUST GONE STRAIGHT TO HER HEAD.

12:32.708 --> 12:34.101
-THANKS.

12:34.231 --> 12:35.885
-SURE.

12:36.799 --> 12:38.322
[MITCH SIGHS]

12:38.453 --> 12:39.933
-I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU
DIDN'T FOLLOW UP ON THIS.

12:40.063 --> 12:41.935
-I'M SORRY, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE HANDLING IT.

12:42.065 --> 12:43.588
-BECAUSE YOU
DIDN'T READ MY MEMO.

12:43.719 --> 12:45.286
-WHY DO YOU HAVE
TO SEND A MEMO?

12:45.416 --> 12:47.027
WHY CAN'T WE JUST TALK?

12:47.157 --> 12:49.507
-ALL YOU HAD TO DO
WAS LOOK AT YOUR DESK.

12:49.638 --> 12:51.771
-OH, WE'RE BICKERING AGAIN.

12:51.901 --> 12:52.946
-WITH GOOD REASON.

12:53.685 --> 12:54.904
YOU LET A PROMOTER
STAGE AN EVENT

12:55.035 --> 12:56.601
WITHOUT EVEN
CHECKING HIS PERMITS.

12:56.732 --> 12:57.777
-YOU KNOW, MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

12:59.082 --> 13:00.257
-THANK YOU.

13:00.388 --> 13:01.781
-NO, NO, NO, NOT
ABOUT THE PERMITS.

13:02.738 --> 13:04.218
ABOUT WORKING TOGETHER.

13:06.002 --> 13:09.832
[GUITAR MUSIC WITH A BEAT]

13:49.959 --> 13:51.700
-HOBESTER!

13:51.831 --> 13:53.006
-HEY, YOU GUYS
ARE JUST IN TIME.

13:53.136 --> 13:54.442
NEELY'S GONNA HEAD OUT.
-ALL RIGHT.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.270
-DO YOU KNOW WHERE
THE PROMOTER IS?

13:56.400 --> 13:57.880
-YEAH, UM...

13:58.011 --> 13:59.273
HE'S RIGHT OVER THERE.

14:04.800 --> 14:07.498
-I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

14:10.414 --> 14:12.025
-MITCH: WHAT?

14:12.155 --> 14:13.374
-THAT'S ADAM.

14:15.985 --> 14:18.379
-YOU MEAN, "ADAM" ADAM?

14:19.771 --> 14:20.860
-WHO'S ADAM?

14:21.643 --> 14:23.036
-MY EX-FIANCE.

14:24.167 --> 14:25.429
-ADAM: HEY!
-SAMANTHA: HEY.

14:25.560 --> 14:28.302
-ADAM: THIS IS A
SURPRISE. HOW ARE YOU?

14:28.432 --> 14:29.999
IS THIS YOUR BEACH?

14:30.130 --> 14:31.479
-UH, YEP.

14:31.609 --> 14:33.133
I HOPE YOU HAVE YOUR PERMITS.

14:33.263 --> 14:34.743
-ACTUALLY, I'M ON MY WAY
TO CITY HALL TO GET 'EM.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.225
-WELL, I WOULD LIKE THEM ON
MY DESK BY THIS AFTERNOON.

14:38.355 --> 14:40.053
-YES, CAPTAIN.

14:40.183 --> 14:42.446
BY THE WAY, YOU LOOK
OUTSTANDING IN YOUR UNIFORM.

14:43.534 --> 14:45.580
-UH, MITCH? HOBIE?

14:45.710 --> 14:47.016
MEET ADAM HERSH.

14:47.147 --> 14:48.104
-HOBIE: HEY.
-ADAM: HEY.

14:48.235 --> 14:49.018
-HOBIE: HOW'S IT GOING?

14:49.149 --> 14:50.628
-HOW YOU DOING?

14:51.542 --> 14:53.370
-HOBIE: LOOKS LIKE
NEELY'S HEAT'S UP.

14:54.067 --> 14:55.764
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT, NEELY!

14:56.460 --> 14:59.115
[ROCK MUSIC]
-SAMANTHA: THERE SHE GOES!

14:59.246 --> 15:01.291
-HOBIE: THERE WE GO,
NEELY, GO FOR IT!

15:01.422 --> 15:02.902
WHOO!

15:05.774 --> 15:07.776
-YEAH, LOOK AT HER DUCK UNDER
THAT WAVE, I TAUGHT HER THAT.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.821
-NICE.

15:11.301 --> 15:12.476
-WHOO!

15:13.390 --> 15:15.915
-HOBIE: ALL RIGHT,
NEELY, NICE LINE, COME ON!

15:16.045 --> 15:18.613
GO FOR THE BARREL
ROLL, YOU GOT IT!

15:18.743 --> 15:20.745
ALL RIGHT! OH!

15:23.487 --> 15:25.489
-OH, THAT HURTS.

15:32.670 --> 15:34.063
-SHE'S FINISHED.

15:39.982 --> 15:44.595
[LOW, SLOW GUITAR MUSIC]

15:46.423 --> 15:47.772
-MITCH: HEY, HEY, GOOD JOB!
[HANDS CLAP]

15:47.903 --> 15:49.949
-HOBIE: NICE TRY.
-BETTER LUCK NEXT TIME.

15:51.167 --> 15:52.952
-DOESN'T SHE GET ANOTHER TRY?

15:53.082 --> 15:54.692
-YOU ONLY GET ONE
CHANCE TO QUALIFY.

15:54.823 --> 15:56.172
-WELL, THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

15:56.303 --> 15:58.958
ONE BAD RIDE AND SHE'S
OUT OF THE COMPETITION?

15:59.088 --> 16:01.221
HOW ARE YOU SUPPOSED TO
DEVELOP NEW TALENT THAT WAY?

16:01.351 --> 16:04.224
-SAMANTHA, YOU'RE NOT
RUNNING THE SHOW ANYMORE.

16:05.007 --> 16:06.400
-WELL, THAT'S PRETTY OBVIOUS,

16:06.530 --> 16:08.054
JUDGING FROM YOUR
PATHETIC TURNOUT.

16:08.750 --> 16:11.013
WOMEN'S BODY BOARDING IS
HUGE ALL OVER THE WORLD,

16:11.144 --> 16:12.362
AND THIS IS ALL YOU COULD DRAW?

16:13.146 --> 16:14.756
-HM.

16:18.238 --> 16:19.674
-WHAT HAPPENED OUT THERE?

16:19.804 --> 16:21.241
IT WAS LIKE YOUR HEAD
WAS SOMEWHERE ELSE.

16:21.371 --> 16:22.720
-IT WAS.

16:23.373 --> 16:24.722
MITCH, I NEED TO ASK A FAVOR.

16:24.853 --> 16:26.594
-MITCH: SURE.

16:26.724 --> 16:28.117
-ONE OF THE GIRLS FROM THE
COMPETITION MAY BE IN TROUBLE.

16:28.248 --> 16:29.684
HER NAME IS JAMIE DUNCAN.

16:29.814 --> 16:31.860
DID YOU READ MY INCIDENT
REPORT FROM YESTERDAY?

16:31.991 --> 16:33.688
-YEAH, ABOUT THAT INCIDENT THAT
HAPPENED ON THE VENICE STRAND.

16:33.818 --> 16:35.037
-RIGHT, WELL ANYWAY, SHE WAS

16:35.168 --> 16:36.473
SUPPOSED TO BE
HERE THIS MORNING,

16:36.604 --> 16:38.084
AND NO ONE HAS ANY
IDEA WHERE SHE IS.

16:38.214 --> 16:40.129
DO YOU STILL HANDLE
CASES LIKE THESE?

16:40.260 --> 16:42.653
I MEAN, I KNOW THERE
ARE NO ALIENS INVOLVED.

16:42.784 --> 16:44.612
[LAUGHS]

16:44.742 --> 16:46.135
-I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN FIND OUT.

16:46.266 --> 16:47.528
SORRY ABOUT THAT, HUH?

16:48.485 --> 16:49.747
-THANKS.

16:52.663 --> 16:54.013
-MAN: CAPTAIN?
-SAMANTHA: YEAH.

16:54.143 --> 16:55.927
-MAN: THERE'S SOMEONE
HERE TO SEE YOU.

16:59.279 --> 17:01.455
-HERE ARE THE
PERMITS, AS REQUESTED.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.022
I HOPE THEY MEET YOUR APPROVAL.

17:05.807 --> 17:08.375
-WELL, EVERYTHING
SEEMS TO BE IN ORDER.

17:08.505 --> 17:11.117
DON'T FORGET YOU ARE
RESPONSIBLE FOR CROWD CONTROL.

17:12.117 --> 17:13.944
NOT THAT THAT
SHOULD BE A PROBLEM.

17:15.295 --> 17:17.252
-AS A MATTER OF FACT, I DID
WANT TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT THAT.

17:17.384 --> 17:18.906
-OH?

17:20.952 --> 17:22.084
-I'LL MAKE IT SHORT AND SWEET.

17:22.214 --> 17:23.477
UH...

17:25.087 --> 17:26.522
I THINK I'M ON THE VERGE
OF GOING UNDER, SAM.

17:27.915 --> 17:29.439
I CAN'T RUN THE
BUSINESS BY MYSELF.

17:30.440 --> 17:31.876
I'M SURE YOU'D BE
THE FIRST TO ADMIT

17:32.007 --> 17:33.748
I HAVE NO SENSE
OF ORGANIZATION.

17:33.878 --> 17:35.358
-WELL, IF YOU'RE HERE
TO ASK ME FOR MONEY,

17:35.489 --> 17:36.707
DON'T WASTE YOUR BREATH.

17:36.838 --> 17:39.884
-MONEY?
NO, I'D NEVER ASK YOU FOR THAT.

17:41.756 --> 17:43.018
-THEN WHAT DO YOU WANT?

17:46.413 --> 17:47.544
I WANT YOU.

17:47.675 --> 17:48.893
I WANT YOU BACK.

17:51.113 --> 17:53.898
AS A PARTNER,
AS A BUSINESS PARTNER.

17:57.989 --> 17:59.774
-YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

18:00.775 --> 18:01.950
-WE MADE A GREAT TEAM.

18:02.081 --> 18:03.299
-WE WEREN'T A TEAM,

18:03.430 --> 18:06.476
WE WERE A TRAVELING
BAR ROOM BRAWL.

18:07.129 --> 18:09.000
-IT'LL BE DIFFERENT THIS TIME.

18:09.740 --> 18:11.177
WE'RE NOT IN LOVE ANYMORE.

18:11.307 --> 18:13.353
OUR RELATIONSHIP WOULD
BE PURELY PLATONIC.

18:13.483 --> 18:15.616
WE COULD FOCUS ALL
ENERGIES ON THE BUSINESS.

18:17.008 --> 18:18.880
YOU'RE ONE OF THE BEST
PROMOTERS I'VE EVER SEEN.

18:19.968 --> 18:21.361
YOU CAN'T JUST SIT THERE

18:21.491 --> 18:23.450
AND LET THOSE GOD-GIVEN
TALENTS GO TO WASTE.

18:25.408 --> 18:27.845
-NOR CAN I JUST WALK AWAY,
I HAVE COMMITMENTS HERE.

18:30.152 --> 18:31.588
-IS MITCH ONE OF
THOSE COMMITMENTS?

18:34.025 --> 18:35.549
-THAT IS NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

18:36.941 --> 18:38.029
-WELL, IF HE IS,

18:38.552 --> 18:40.467
I WOULD GIVE MY OFFER
SERIOUS CONSIDERATION.

18:40.597 --> 18:41.598
AFTER ALL,

18:43.513 --> 18:45.559
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN VERY GOOD AT
MIXING BUSINESS AND PLEASURE.

18:52.087 --> 18:54.785
-CODY: SORRY TO HEAR YOU DIDN'T
QUALIFY FOR THE WILD WAHINE.

18:54.916 --> 18:56.222
YOU MUST BE PRETTY BUMMED OUT.

18:56.352 --> 18:58.572
-OH, IT'S NOT THE
END OF THE WORLD.

18:58.702 --> 19:00.704
-THE IMPORTANT THING IS
NOT TO GET DOWN ON YOURSELF.

19:00.835 --> 19:03.664
MY FIRST SWIM MEET, I FINISHED
DEAD LAST IN EVERY EVENT.

19:04.317 --> 19:06.493
BUT THE VERY NEXT DAY,
I WAS RIGHT BACK IN THE POOL.

19:06.623 --> 19:09.017
-IT'S ALL ABOUT DEDI--
-DID YOU FIND HER?

19:11.237 --> 19:12.934
-NO.

19:13.064 --> 19:14.109
NO ONE AT THE HOTEL HAS SEEN
HER SINCE SHE CHECKED IN.

19:14.936 --> 19:16.285
--CHAMBERMAID SAID HER BED

19:16.416 --> 19:18.157
HASN'T BEEN SLEPT IN
THE LAST TWO NIGHTS.

19:18.287 --> 19:19.767
--SHE'S OUT ON THE STREETS.

19:19.897 --> 19:22.465
-ALL OF HER BELONGINGS
WERE STILL IN HER ROOM.

19:24.032 --> 19:25.425
-INCLUDING THIS.

19:25.555 --> 19:26.600
-WHAT IS IT?

19:26.730 --> 19:28.776
-LITHIUM, A FULL PRESCRIPTION.

19:28.906 --> 19:30.169
-CODY: WHAT'S LITHIUM?

19:31.170 --> 19:32.345
-IT'S USED TO TREAT
MANIC DEPRESSION.

19:32.997 --> 19:35.565
IF SHE STOPPED TAKING THIS,
THIS COULD EXPLAIN HER BEHAVIOR.

19:36.914 --> 19:38.394
-MY SISTER WAS
A MANIC DEPRESSIVE.

19:39.308 --> 19:41.136
I THOUGHT I RECOGNIZED
THE SYMPTOMS IN JAMIE.

19:41.267 --> 19:43.312
THE DELUSIONAL
BEHAVIOR, THE PARANOIA.

19:44.487 --> 19:45.749
WE'VE GOTTA FIND HER, MITCH,

19:45.880 --> 19:47.316
BEFORE SOMETHING
TERRIBLE HAPPENS.

19:48.796 --> 19:53.192
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

20:02.679 --> 20:04.507
[TRASH CAN BANGS]

20:06.944 --> 20:08.468
[MEN MUTTERING]

20:09.991 --> 20:11.122
-WOMAN: ANY LUCK, FELLAS?

20:11.253 --> 20:12.559
-HEY, SHUT UP OVER THERE,

20:12.689 --> 20:14.038
I'M TRYING TO GET SOME SLEEP!

20:19.566 --> 20:21.045
STUPID LOSERS!

20:21.176 --> 20:22.308
GET A REAL JOB.

20:23.178 --> 20:24.571
WHAT ARE YOU, DEAF?

20:24.701 --> 20:26.573
GET THE HELL OUTTA HERE!

20:29.750 --> 20:32.231
-MAN: GET OUTTA HERE!

20:34.929 --> 20:37.236
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

20:41.892 --> 20:44.243
-WOMAN: OH! HEY...

20:46.810 --> 20:49.378
-WOMAN:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? RUDE!

20:50.727 --> 20:52.251
-HEY, HEY!

20:52.381 --> 20:53.730
HEY, WHAT DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE DOING?

20:53.861 --> 20:55.079
HEY!

20:55.210 --> 20:56.820
COME ON, LADY, PUT
THAT STUFF BACK.

20:56.951 --> 20:59.040
I DON'T WANT ANY TROUBLE.
COME BACK HERE!

20:59.170 --> 21:00.998
[JAMIE GRUNTS]
GIMME THOSE SHIRTS!

21:01.129 --> 21:03.087
I DON'T WANT ANY TROUBLE.
-JAMIE: THEY'RE MINE! NOT YOURS!

21:06.830 --> 21:08.223
-MAN: HEY, GET BACK HERE!

21:09.093 --> 21:11.966
GET BACK HERE!
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?

21:12.096 --> 21:13.315
-JAMIE: GET AWAY FROM ME!
GET BACK!

21:13.446 --> 21:15.099
GET AWAY FROM ME,
I'M WARNING YOU!

21:15.230 --> 21:16.971
-LADY, I JUST WANT MY T-SHIRTS!

21:17.101 --> 21:19.016
[JAMIE LAUGHS, MANICALLY]
-NO, NEVER!

21:19.147 --> 21:20.627
NEVER!

21:20.757 --> 21:22.150
-MAN: JUST GIVE
ME MY T-SHIRTS.

21:22.281 --> 21:24.587
-JAMIE: GET BACK.
-YOU, JUST GIMME THEM!

21:26.850 --> 21:28.504
[MAN YELLS]

21:32.073 --> 21:33.509
COME BACK HERE!

21:33.640 --> 21:35.032
HEY, STOP HER!

21:35.163 --> 21:36.033
STOP HER!

21:36.164 --> 21:37.600
SHE'S GOT MY...

21:37.731 --> 21:39.472
SHE STOLE MY T-SHIRTS!

21:40.124 --> 21:42.605
SOMEBODY HELP! STOP HER!

21:43.389 --> 21:46.261
STOP THIS GIRL!
STOP HER!

21:46.392 --> 21:48.742
SOMEBODY HELP!
GET HER!

21:48.872 --> 21:50.570
DON'T LET HER GET AWAY!
-CODY: NEELY, LOOK.

21:52.049 --> 21:53.050
-IT'S JAMIE.

21:53.181 --> 21:54.269
-LET'S GO GET HER.

21:54.400 --> 21:57.490
[SIREN WAILING]

21:57.620 --> 22:00.406
-MAN: STOP HER!
DON'T LET HER GET AWAY!

22:00.536 --> 22:02.408
STOP! STOP HER!

22:02.538 --> 22:07.021
[COUGHS]

22:17.814 --> 22:20.469
-NEELY: JAMIE!
JAMIE, STOP!

22:28.738 --> 22:30.610
[JAMIE YELLS]

22:30.740 --> 22:31.959
-CODY: WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

22:32.089 --> 22:34.744
HEY, HEY, CALM DOWN.
CALM DOWN!

22:36.267 --> 22:37.268
KNOCK IT OFF!

22:37.399 --> 22:40.837
-STOP IT!
STOP IT!

22:40.968 --> 22:42.796
-CODY: GET HER, GET HER IN!

22:43.971 --> 22:45.973
[JAMIE YELLS]
-LET GO!

22:46.103 --> 22:47.104
-CODY: THAT'S ENOUGH!

22:49.759 --> 22:51.195
-JAMIE: LET GO!
-NEELY: STOP!

22:51.326 --> 22:52.327
-JAMIE: LET GO!
-NEELY: STOP IT.

22:52.458 --> 22:57.288
-JAMIE: LET GO! AH!

22:59.421 --> 23:00.814
-CODY: HOW DID SHE GO
FROM BEING SO HYPER

23:00.944 --> 23:02.119
TO BEING SO ZONED OUT?

23:02.816 --> 23:04.905
-WELL, THAT'S WHAT, MANIC
DEPRESSION IS ALL ABOUT.

23:05.035 --> 23:06.515
YOU SWING BACK AND FORTH

23:06.646 --> 23:08.430
BETWEEN EUPHORIC HIGHS
AND DEBILITATING LOWS.

23:08.561 --> 23:11.085
IT'S CAUSED BY A CHEMICAL
IMBALANCE IN THE BRAIN.

23:13.261 --> 23:14.784
-WELL, HER VITALS ARE FINE.

23:14.915 --> 23:16.699
ASIDE FROM A FEW
CUTS AND BRUISES.

23:16.830 --> 23:17.787
[VELCRO RIPS]

23:17.918 --> 23:19.136
I THINK SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

23:19.267 --> 23:19.963
-SO WHAT'RE WE
GONNA DO WITH HER?

23:20.094 --> 23:21.400
CALL THE POLICE?

23:21.530 --> 23:23.271
-I'M GONNA CONTACT
HER FAMILY, FIRST.

23:23.402 --> 23:24.794
-SHE'S FROM HAWAII.

23:24.925 --> 23:27.101
-CAPTAIN, IF SHE'S
ANYTHING LIKE MY SISTER,

23:27.231 --> 23:28.842
SHE PROBABLY LEADS A NORMAL LIFE

23:28.972 --> 23:30.539
WHEN SHE'S ON HER MEDICATION.

23:30.670 --> 23:32.541
-YEAH, BUT HOW YOU
GONNA GET HER TO TAKE IT?

23:32.672 --> 23:33.760
I MEAN, LOOK AT HER.

23:35.326 --> 23:36.240
-WELL, FIRST,
WE NEED TO FIND OUT

23:36.371 --> 23:37.894
WHY SHE STOPPED TAKING IT.

23:41.332 --> 23:43.770
YOU'RE SAFE NOW, JAMIE.
NO ONE'S GONNA HURT YOU, OKAY?

23:43.900 --> 23:45.119
WE'RE HERE TO HELP.

23:46.729 --> 23:48.209
-I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

23:49.210 --> 23:50.254
AND THOSE AREN'T MY PILLS.

23:54.607 --> 23:55.869
ARE YOU IN CHARGE, HERE?

23:56.609 --> 23:58.437
YOU'RE HOLDING ME
AGAINST MY WILL.

23:58.567 --> 24:00.395
I WANNA GO HOME.

24:00.526 --> 24:02.092
-LOOK, WHERE DO YOU LIVE?

24:02.223 --> 24:03.833
-NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

24:03.964 --> 24:05.356
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

24:05.487 --> 24:07.010
-CODY: WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
-NEELY: WAIT, JAMIE!

24:07.141 --> 24:08.664
-JAMIE: LET GO OF MY ARM!
-NEELY: STOP IT!

24:08.795 --> 24:10.927
-JAMIE: LET GO!
-NEELY: STOP IT.

24:11.058 --> 24:12.712
-NO!

24:12.842 --> 24:14.061
-LET'S GET HER IN THE SHOWERS.
-YOU CAN'T KEEP ME HERE!

24:14.191 --> 24:16.716
-JAMIE: NO! NO!

24:18.674 --> 24:21.895
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS TO ME?
[WATER RUNS]

24:22.417 --> 24:23.897
[JAMIE SOBS]
-BECAUSE...

24:24.027 --> 24:26.116
YOU'RE THE BEST BODY
BOARDER IN THE WORLD.

24:26.247 --> 24:28.989
-AND I'M NOT GONNA LET
YOU THROW YOUR LIFE AWAY.

24:30.294 --> 24:33.472
JAMIE, I CARE ABOUT
WHAT HAPPENS TO YOU.

24:33.602 --> 24:35.082
EVEN IF YOU DON'T.

24:53.796 --> 24:55.276
BE CAREFUL, IT'S HOT.

24:55.406 --> 24:56.625
-THANKS.

25:03.632 --> 25:05.286
DID SHE LOOK LIKE YOU?

25:05.416 --> 25:06.635
-WHO?

25:07.506 --> 25:08.550
-YOUR SISTER.

25:08.681 --> 25:09.725
-OH.

25:10.334 --> 25:12.075
[SIGHS]

25:12.206 --> 25:14.904
WE HAD THE SAME EYES, BUT
HER HAIR WAS DARK LIKE YOURS.

25:16.253 --> 25:17.516
-WHAT HAPPENED TO HER?

25:20.431 --> 25:22.738
-WELL, UH, SHE WAS A MUSICIAN.

25:23.826 --> 25:26.350
SHE WROTE THE MOST
BEAUTIFUL SONGS.

25:27.308 --> 25:30.441
BUT SHE WAS DIFFICULT TO LIVE
WITH, AS YOU MIGHT IMAGINE.

25:32.879 --> 25:34.141
SHE SAID HER MOOD SWINGS

25:34.271 --> 25:35.664
WERE PART OF HER
CREATIVE PROCESS.

25:38.145 --> 25:40.495
AND EVEN AFTER SHE WAS
DIAGNOSED AS A MANIC DEPRESSIVE,

25:41.844 --> 25:43.585
SHE REFUSED TO ACCEPT IT.

25:45.282 --> 25:48.938
SO SHE, TOO, STOPPED
TAKING HER LITHIUM.

25:51.332 --> 25:52.768
AND THEN ONE DAY,

25:53.813 --> 25:55.641
SHE WAS HAVING A FIGHT
WITH HER BOYFRIEND,

25:56.946 --> 25:58.208
AND SHE RAN INTO THE
MIDDLE OF THE STREET

25:58.339 --> 25:59.340
TO GET AWAY FROM HIM.

25:59.993 --> 26:01.342
AND UH...

26:03.039 --> 26:06.782
THE DRIVER OF THE CAR
NEVER SAW HER COMING.

26:09.742 --> 26:10.960
I'M SORRY.

26:13.441 --> 26:14.834
-JAMIE,

26:15.617 --> 26:18.838
WHY DID YOU STOP
TAKING YOUR MEDICATION?

26:23.494 --> 26:26.454
-YOU KNOW, WHEN I FIRST
STARTED BODY BOARDING,

26:28.848 --> 26:30.414
IT WAS FOR THE FUN, YOU KNOW?

26:30.545 --> 26:31.633
THE RUSH.

26:35.245 --> 26:40.207
AND NOW IT'S
ENDORSEMENTS AND SPONSORS,

26:40.816 --> 26:42.818
PRESS AGENTS, LAWYERS.

26:45.342 --> 26:47.214
I DON'T KNOW, I JUST...

26:49.042 --> 26:51.131
THERE'S SO MUCH PRESSURE.

26:54.308 --> 26:55.614
I COULDN'T HANDLE IT, I,

26:57.224 --> 26:58.791
I GUESS I JUST LOST CONTROL.

27:00.227 --> 27:03.839
-WELL, HEY, YOU SEEM
PRETTY IN CONTROL NOW.

27:05.667 --> 27:07.538
FEELS GOOD, DOESN'T IT?

27:13.893 --> 27:16.809
-MITCH. MITCH.

27:18.245 --> 27:19.638
HOW'S JAMIE DOING?

27:19.768 --> 27:21.117
-MUCH BETTER, NEELY GOT
HER TO TAKE THE LITHIUM.

27:21.248 --> 27:22.858
-OH, GREAT.
-AS A MATTER OF FACT,

27:22.989 --> 27:24.468
SHE MIGHT BE COMPETING IN
THE TOURNAMENT TOMORROW.

27:24.599 --> 27:25.948
-WELL, NOT UNTIL
SHE SEES A DOCTOR.

27:26.079 --> 27:27.036
I'M NOT GONNA LET HER COMPETE

27:27.167 --> 27:27.994
WITHOUT A CLEAN BILL OF HEALTH.

27:28.124 --> 27:29.125
-HOW CAN YOU STOP HER?

27:29.256 --> 27:30.083
-I'M PROMOTING THE TOURNAMENT.

27:30.213 --> 27:31.780
-WHAT?

27:31.911 --> 27:33.390
-ADAM AND I ARE GOING BACK
INTO BUSINESS TOGETHER.

27:33.521 --> 27:36.219
-WHOA, WAIT A MINUTE, HERE.

27:37.525 --> 27:39.135
DOES THIS MEAN YOU'RE
QUITTING BAYWATCH?

27:39.266 --> 27:40.963
-I CAN STILL WORK WEEKENDS
AND FILL IN OCCASIONALLY.

27:41.094 --> 27:43.183
-DON'T YOU THINK WE SHOULDA
TALKED ABOUT THIS, FIRST?

27:43.313 --> 27:44.750
-MITCH, THIS SOLVES
ALL OUR PROBLEMS.

27:44.880 --> 27:46.447
NOW WORK WON'T INTERFERE
WITH OUR RELATIONSHIP.

27:46.577 --> 27:47.491
-WHAT ABOUT ADAM?

27:47.622 --> 27:49.058
WON'T ADAM GET IN THE WAY?

27:49.929 --> 27:51.365
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT ADAM,

27:51.495 --> 27:53.062
IT'S STRICTLY BUSINESS.

27:53.193 --> 27:56.065
HE'S ON THE VERGE OF
BANKRUPTCY, HE'S DESPERATE.

27:56.196 --> 27:57.937
AND I'M BUYING BACK MY
SHARE OF THE COMPANY

27:58.067 --> 27:59.982
FOR A THIRD OF WHAT
I SOLD IT TO HIM FOR.

28:00.113 --> 28:02.202
-SOUNDS LIKE YOU
GOT A HECK OF A DEAL.

28:02.985 --> 28:05.118
-I'VE GOTTA GO COMPOSE
MY LETTER TO THE CHIEF.

28:07.250 --> 28:09.339
PLEASE UNDERSTAND
WHY I'M DOING THIS.

28:09.470 --> 28:13.517
[MELANCHOLY PIANO MUSIC]

28:18.871 --> 28:20.916
[UPTEMPO BACKGROUND MUSIC]

28:21.047 --> 28:22.265
-GARY!

28:24.093 --> 28:25.834
GARY, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET MY PARTNER.

28:25.965 --> 28:27.488
THIS IS ADAM HERSH.

28:27.618 --> 28:28.619
-GARY HALL.

28:28.750 --> 28:30.491
-THE OLYMPIC GOLD MEDALIST?

28:30.621 --> 28:33.059
-HE WILL BE PRESENTING THE
TROPHY TO THE WINNER, TODAY.

28:34.582 --> 28:36.018
ARE YOU HUNGRY?
THERE'S SO MUCH FOOD.

28:36.149 --> 28:36.976
GO AHEAD AND HELP YOURSELF.

28:37.106 --> 28:38.325
-GARY: THANKS.

28:38.455 --> 28:39.674
-NICE MEETING YOU, GARY.

28:39.805 --> 28:40.936
-HI.

28:41.981 --> 28:44.461
-YOU ARE INCREDIBLE!

28:44.592 --> 28:45.941
I'M IN AWE.

28:46.072 --> 28:47.464
-YOU ARE IN DEBT.

28:47.595 --> 28:49.423
JUST PUT $10,000 ON
YOUR LINE OF CREDIT.

28:49.553 --> 28:51.425
-THAT'S OKAY, WE'LL
MAKE TWICE THAT TODAY.

28:52.339 --> 28:55.342
WE REALLY DO MAKE
A GREAT TEAM, DON'T WE?

28:57.170 --> 28:58.649
-UH, THERE'S JAMIE.

29:02.479 --> 29:03.350
-I GOTTA GET IT TOGETHER
WITH THIS PRINCESS.

29:03.480 --> 29:04.917
-YOU KNOW, ADAM,

29:05.047 --> 29:06.701
IT MIGHT BE A GOOD IDEA
IF WE LEFT HER ALONE,

29:06.832 --> 29:08.529
SHE'S GOT SO MUCH GOING ON
WITHOUT YOU HOUNDING HER.

29:09.573 --> 29:11.227
-OKAY.
-HEY SANDY, SANDY!

29:11.358 --> 29:12.533
I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET ADAM HERSH.

29:13.403 --> 29:15.231
