32:32.428 --> 32:33.908
-NEWMIE!

32:34.039 --> 32:35.605
NEWMIE!

32:35.736 --> 32:38.217
I THOUGHT YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO BE A ROLE MODEL?

32:39.218 --> 32:41.089
GONNA LET THE LOVE OF YOUR
LIFE WALK AWAY LIKE THAT

32:41.220 --> 32:42.873
WITHOUT EVEN TRYING
TO TALK TO HER.

32:44.005 --> 32:45.659
MAN, THAT IS LAME!

32:47.052 --> 32:49.315
-ACTUALLY, I WAS
JUST ABOUT READY

32:49.445 --> 32:51.143
TO GO DOWN AND INTRODUCE MYSELF.

32:51.273 --> 32:53.362
-WHAT?
OH, MY, MAN!

32:53.493 --> 32:54.668
THAT'S IT, BRO!

32:54.798 --> 32:56.496
YOU GOT THE EYE
OF THE TIGER, NOW!

32:57.105 --> 32:58.628
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

32:58.759 --> 33:00.979
-WATCH CLOSELY, KID, YOU
MAY WANNA TAKE SOME NOTES.

33:01.109 --> 33:05.592
[BEACHGOERS CHATTER]

33:06.593 --> 33:08.203
-EXCUSE ME.

33:08.334 --> 33:10.118
THIS WAS JUST BLOWING
AWAY, IS IT YOUR MAGAZINE?

33:10.249 --> 33:12.686
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

33:13.904 --> 33:15.428
-YOU DON'T SPEAK ENGLISH?

33:18.561 --> 33:20.172
-UNO MOMENTO.

33:20.302 --> 33:22.435
HEY, MANNY! COME HERE.

33:24.741 --> 33:27.005
-MANNY: WHAT'S GOING ON?
-AH, SHE ONLY SPEAKS SPANISH.

33:27.135 --> 33:28.354
I NEED YOU TO TRANSLATE.

33:29.398 --> 33:31.313
-SHOOT, GO AHEAD.

33:31.879 --> 33:34.577
-WELL, UH, ASK HER IF SHE'D
LIKE TO HAVE DINNER WITH ME.

33:34.708 --> 33:35.752
-DINNER.

33:48.330 --> 33:49.636
-WHAT DID SHE SAY?

33:50.854 --> 33:52.726
-SHE SAID THAT SHE FINDS
YOU VERY INTERESTING.

34:10.657 --> 34:12.050
-YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE TRANSLATING.

34:13.920 --> 34:16.054
-SHE SAYS THAT SHE WOULD
LOVE TO HAVE DINNER WITH YOU,

34:17.925 --> 34:19.579
BUT SHE'S VERY BUSY TONIGHT.

34:20.319 --> 34:22.495
-WELL, UH, WHAT
ABOUT TOMORROW NIGHT?

34:23.364 --> 34:24.931
-MANNY:
TOMORROW NIGHT, UM...

34:26.498 --> 34:30.024
-HELP!
[SUSIE GASPS]

34:30.155 --> 34:31.460
-I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

34:31.591 --> 34:34.855
[EXCITING MUSIC]
-SUSIE: HELP! HELP!

34:40.947 --> 34:42.993
HELP, HELP!

34:50.043 --> 34:52.002
-NEWMIE:
ARE YOU IN TROUBLE?

34:52.132 --> 34:53.960
HEY!

34:54.092 --> 34:55.963
-MAN: IT'S
GETTING ROUGH OUT THERE!

34:56.746 --> 34:58.400
-NEWMIE: IT'S
OKAY, I'VE GOT YOU.

35:01.011 --> 35:02.752
HANG ON. I'LL GET YOU IN.

35:02.883 --> 35:04.406
-OH, MY GOD.

35:15.678 --> 35:17.985
-WOMAN: OH, MY BABY!
OH, GOD!

35:18.116 --> 35:20.683
OH! SUSIE, SWEETHEART!
-NEWMIE: YOU OKAY?

35:20.814 --> 35:23.643
-WOMAN: OH, BABY, HONEY.

35:23.773 --> 35:26.167
ARE YOU OKAY?
OH, MY BABY.

35:26.298 --> 35:28.256
SWEETHEART, WHAT WERE YOU
DOING OUT THERE BY YOURSELF?

35:41.269 --> 35:46.492
[UPTEMPO MUSIC]
[WAVES CRASH]

35:53.847 --> 35:59.287
[ONLOOKERS APPLAUD]

35:59.418 --> 36:02.595
-ALL RIGHT, JAMIE
NEEDS A 9.5 TO WIN THIS.

36:02.725 --> 36:03.857
-OKAY.

36:16.609 --> 36:18.393
-YEAH!

36:30.318 --> 36:32.842
ALL RIGHT!
-NEELY: JAMIE, WHOO!

36:32.973 --> 36:38.196
[ONLOOKERS APPLAUD AND CHEER]

36:44.680 --> 36:47.988
YES! YOU DID IT!

36:50.730 --> 36:52.166
ARE YOU OKAY WITH ALL THIS?

36:52.297 --> 36:54.690
-YEAH, I THINK I CAN HANDLE IT.

36:54.821 --> 36:58.433
[CAMERAS CLICK]

36:58.564 --> 37:00.218
THANK YOU.

37:02.698 --> 37:04.439
THANK YOU.

37:05.397 --> 37:09.749
THANK YOU.
[CROWD CHEERS]

37:15.233 --> 37:16.625
YES!

37:28.333 --> 37:30.335
-ADAM: SO, HOW DOES IT
FEEL TO BE BACK IN ACTION?

37:30.465 --> 37:31.727
-EXHAUSTING.

37:33.816 --> 37:35.253
-TO A JOB WELL DONE.

37:39.518 --> 37:41.259
BRINGS BACK
MEMORIES, DOESN'T IT?

37:43.478 --> 37:44.958
-YOU KNOW, I KEPT THINKING ABOUT

37:45.088 --> 37:47.047
THAT OVER-THE-LINE
TOURNAMENT IN SAN DIEGO.

37:48.396 --> 37:49.876
-DON'T GO GETTING
SENTIMENTAL ON ME, OKAY?

37:50.006 --> 37:51.530
-WHY NOT?

37:51.660 --> 37:52.879
WE HAD SOME GREAT
TIMES TOGETHER.

37:53.009 --> 37:54.881
-ADAM, DON'T DO THIS TO ME.

37:55.011 --> 37:56.970
WE AGREED THIS WAS GONNA
BE COMPLETELY PLATONIC.

37:57.100 --> 37:58.406
THAT WAS PART OF THE DEAL.

37:58.537 --> 37:59.973
-YEAH, STILL, I THOUGHT,

38:00.495 --> 38:03.324
MAYBE WE COULD DO
A LITTLE RENEGOTIATING.

38:03.455 --> 38:05.195
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

38:06.066 --> 38:08.547
-I CAN'T HELP IT.
I STILL LOVE YOU.

38:08.677 --> 38:10.636
-NO, YOU DON'T.
-YES, I DO.

38:11.637 --> 38:12.942
-WE HAVE AN IDEAL
SITUATION, HERE,

38:13.073 --> 38:14.553
WHY ARE YOU TRYING
TO SCREW THIS UP?

38:16.772 --> 38:18.078
-I'M SORRY.

38:18.208 --> 38:20.298
I THOUGHT IT WAS
OVER, I REALLY DID.

38:20.950 --> 38:22.387
AND THEN I SAW YOU
THE OTHER DAY

38:22.517 --> 38:23.779
IN THAT UNIFORM, AND I...

38:23.910 --> 38:25.651
-IT IS OVER, YOU KNOW WHAT?

38:25.781 --> 38:28.915
IT IS OVER ON EVERY LEVEL,
IN EVERY WAY, SHAPE AND FORM.

38:29.568 --> 38:31.309
HAVE A NICE LIFE.

38:36.488 --> 38:38.490
-THAT'S WHAT I GET
FOR BEING HONEST.

38:38.620 --> 38:41.406
[EASY LISTENING MUSIC]

38:44.278 --> 38:45.366
-SAMANTHA: BAD NEWS.

38:45.932 --> 38:47.020
-MITCH: OH, NO, WHAT NOW?

38:47.150 --> 38:48.369
-SAMANTHA: I'M NOT QUITTING.

38:48.500 --> 38:50.328
-MITCH: OH, REALLY,
WHAT HAPPENED?

38:50.458 --> 38:54.157
-SAMANTHA: IT'S A LONG STORY.
LET'S JUST SAY THAT I FOUND OUT

38:54.288 --> 38:55.898
THAT SOMETIMES THE
SOLUTION TO A PROBLEM

38:56.029 --> 38:57.683
CAN BE WORSE THAN
THE PROBLEM ITSELF.

38:57.813 --> 38:58.727
[MITCH LAUGHS]

38:58.858 --> 39:00.250
-I COULDA TOLD YOU THAT.

39:01.948 --> 39:03.210
-I JUST WANNA LET YOU KNOW

39:03.341 --> 39:04.385
THAT I'M GONNA DO
EVERYTHING I CAN

39:04.516 --> 39:05.604
TO MAKE THIS THING WORK.

39:05.734 --> 39:06.996
OFF DUTY, AND ON.

39:07.127 --> 39:08.476
I'VE REARRANGED OUR SCHEDULES

39:08.607 --> 39:10.652
SO WE ONLY HAVE
TWO SHIFTS A WEEK TOGETHER.

39:11.349 --> 39:12.741
-THAT SOUNDS MANAGEABLE.

39:12.872 --> 39:14.134
-SAMANTHA: I HOPE SO.

39:14.264 --> 39:15.614
-ME TOO.

39:16.223 --> 39:18.486
-I DON'T SUPPOSE HOBIE'S
GOING OUT TONIGHT, IS HE?

39:19.139 --> 39:22.229
-NO, NO, HE'S GOT
A TON OF HOMEWORK.

39:24.318 --> 39:26.364
BUT I DO KNOW A LITTLE UM,

39:26.494 --> 39:29.236
SECLUDED COVE AROUND THE CORNER.

39:30.106 --> 39:30.977
RACE YOU.

39:31.107 --> 39:32.239
[BOTH LAUGH]

39:49.561 --> 39:50.823
-CODY?

39:50.953 --> 39:52.477
CODY, WOULD IT BE
POSSIBLE FOR YOU

39:52.607 --> 39:53.739
TO TAKE NEWMIE'S SCHEDULE
THE NEXT TWO WEEKS?

39:53.869 --> 39:55.828
-SURE.
-GREAT.

39:55.958 --> 39:58.396
THEN I CAN PUT JORDAN
AND DONNA IN YOUR SPOTS,

39:58.526 --> 40:00.528
AND THEN SWITCH C.J.
AND CAROLINE,

40:00.659 --> 40:01.877
AND THAT SHOULD WORK OUT.

40:02.008 --> 40:03.401
-WHAT'S WRONG WITH NEWMIE?

40:03.531 --> 40:04.924
HE FINALLY GOING IN FOR
THAT KNEE OPERATION?

40:05.054 --> 40:06.142
-YOU DIDN'T HEAR?

40:06.273 --> 40:07.579
-CODY: WHAT?

40:07.709 --> 40:08.797
-REMEMBER THE GIRL
IN THE BINOCULARS?

40:08.928 --> 40:09.842
-CODY: YEAH.

40:09.972 --> 40:11.452
-SHE IS TAKING HIM HOME

40:11.583 --> 40:13.976
-TO MEET HER PARENTS
IN GUADALAJARA.

40:14.803 --> 40:16.370
-GUADALAJARA?

40:16.501 --> 40:17.893
YOU'RE KIDDING ME!
-SAMANTHA: UH-UH.

40:18.024 --> 40:19.765
ACTUALLY, THEY ARE
JUST ABOUT TO LEAVE.

40:19.895 --> 40:21.549
IF WE HURRY,
WE MIGHT JUST CATCH 'EM.

40:22.811 --> 40:23.986
-NEWMIE!

40:39.175 --> 40:40.438
-WHAT'S MANNY
DOING IN THE BACK?

40:40.568 --> 40:42.483
-HE'S GOING ALONG
AS A TRANSLATOR.

40:44.398 --> 40:45.921
-GUESS I MUST'VE
WRITTEN HIM OFF TOO SOON.

40:46.052 --> 40:48.358
-YEAH, WELL, GUESS HE'S
STILL GOT THE TOUCH.

40:48.881 --> 40:53.538
[PIANO MUSIC WITH A BEAT]

40:54.582 --> 40:56.323
-ADIOS, AMIGO!

40:57.150 --> 40:58.978
-VAYA CON DIOS!

41:03.243 --> 41:05.854
[BOTH LAUGH]

